    "body": "It's useful to know what the real layout looks like in the type.\n\n`repr(C)` almost demostrates the type layout, so everyone can figure out the field order and paddings.\n\nBut the layouts of default `repr(Rust)` and codegen structures (closures, async fn etc) are not guaranteed, but it doesn't mean it should be hidden from low-level code writers.\n\nIt'd also be useful to know the niches for every type in the code, like https://niche.rs/ does.",
